history.content:
kinda panicking...I was originally enrolled in 16b/170/188 (170/188 were waitlisted because I haven't declared yet). My position on the 170 waitlist was 165. I decided to swap to 61c because of the prerequisites I need later on and it felt like the smarter move. It said open when enrolling for 61c, so I made the mistake of thinking I would be automatically enrolled, so I enrolled and now have position 102 on 61c waitlist. What is this chance of getting off the waitlist for 61c? Or for it to expand again? I am really worried now because if I re-enrolled into 170 I would go to position 373 I believe. I am not sure if I messed up and won't have either class now. Does anyone know what can happen or what I should do? Did I just mess up big time?

On berkeleyTime it says last spring had a size of 744, is this likely to be the case with the newer budget? If not, what should I do?

EDIT: Didn't they announce budget was expanded and enrollment would be similar to last spring?
